What you need to know:

The tournament was initially known as the Tri Nations, until Argentina became the fourth team in 2012.It has now reverted to its old name, for this year at least, after South Africa withdrew citing a lack of match practice.New Zealand's All Blacks won the inaugural edition in 1996 and have dominated since, claiming another 15 titles.Australia and South Africa have won four times each.The tournament doesn't start until Saturday, but the Wallabies and All Blacks have already seen action contesting the annual Bledisloe Cup, played since 1931.